Assessment 3
Topic: Core Prompting Techniques: Teaching AI to Think, Evaluate & Decide
Submitted By: Aman Dekate
Introduction
Core prompting techniques help AI solve complex tasks by encouraging structured reasoning, evaluation, and decision-making. This assessment focuses on Chain-of-Thought (CoT), ReAct, and Self-Consistency prompting and demonstrates their practical use through solved exercises.
Chain-of-Thought (CoT) Prompting
Exercise 1: Divisibility by 9
Rule: A number is divisible by 9 if the sum of its digits is divisible by 9.
Step 1: 4 + 5 = 9.
Step 2: 9 is divisible by 9.
Final Answer: Yes, 45 is divisible by 9.
Exercise 2: Marketing Message Evaluation
Target Audience: Businesses looking for ERP solutions.
Missing Information: Specific benefits, proof, and measurable outcomes.
Evaluation: The statement is too generic.
Improved Version: 'Our cloud-based ERP automates business operations, improves productivity, and reduces manual work, helping organizations save time and increase efficiency.'
Exercise 3: Feature-to-Benefit Thinking
Cloud-based means the ERP is hosted online and accessed through the internet.
Benefits: (1) Access from anywhere. (2) Lower IT infrastructure and maintenance costs.
Conclusion: A cloud-based ERP offers flexibility, scalability, and cost savings.
Exercise 4: Decision Making
Excel Limitations: Manual updates, poor collaboration, limited scalability.
ERP Advantages: Centralized data, automation, real-time reporting.
Decision: An ERP system is the better long-term solution for a growing startup.
Exercise 5: Problem Analysis
Root Cause: Manual data entry.
Reason for Delays: Repeated work and human errors slow operations.
Solution: Implement an ERP with automated workflows and centralized data.
ReAct (Reason + Act) Prompting
Exercise 1
Weakness: 'Our software is good' is vague.
Missing: Benefits and value.
Improved: 'Our ERP software streamlines operations, reduces manual work, and improves business productivity.'
Exercise 2
Weakness: 'Worked on testing' lacks detail.
Improved: 'Performed functional and regression testing using Jira, identified defects, and improved software quality.'
Exercise 3
Weakness: 'Click here' provides no motivation.
Improved: 'Book your free ERP demo today and discover how to improve your business efficiency.'
Exercise 4
Weakness: Lacks benefits.
Target User: Business owners and managers.
Improved: 'Our ERP solution helps businesses automate operations, improve visibility, and reduce operational costs.'
Exercise 5
Missing Details: System, page, duration, browser, environment.
Improved: 'The dashboard takes about 12 seconds to load after login in Chrome on Windows 11, affecting user productivity.'
Self-Consistency Prompting
Exercise 1
Version 1: ERP manages business processes.
Review: Too brief.
Improved: ERP software integrates finance, HR, inventory, and sales into one system, improving efficiency and decision-making.
Exercise 2
Answer 1: ERP manages data.
Answer 2: ERP integrates business departments.
Answer 3: ERP automates and connects core business processes.
Best: Answer 3 because it is the most complete and clear.
Refined: ERP integrates and automates finance, HR, inventory, and sales, improving collaboration and productivity.
Exercise 3
Subject 1: You're Invited to an ERP Demo
Subject 2: See How ERP Can Improve Your Business
Better: Subject 2.
Refined: Join Our Free ERP Demo and Discover Smarter Business Management.
Exercise 4
Original: Cloud computing provides online computing resources.
Simplified: Cloud computing lets you use software and store files over the internet instead of only on your computer.
Exercise 5
Initial: ERP helps managers.
Improved: ERP provides managers with real-time reports, better operational visibility, and data-driven insights for faster decision-making.
Key Learning
• Chain-of-Thought improves logical reasoning.
• ReAct combines analysis with action to improve responses.
• Self-Consistency compares multiple answers to produce the most reliable output.
• Selecting the right prompting technique improves AI performance.
Conclusion
Core prompting techniques enable AI to think logically, evaluate information, and make better decisions. Understanding these methods helps create accurate, consistent, and reliable AI-generated responses in real-world applications.

